reviews.reviewText:
I really like my new Echo Dot. It is easy to set it up, works great with other smart devices and it's pretty intelligent too. It is great for remembering things, for entertainment, alarms, playing music and many more things. It does a surprisingly good job answering questions. It's a great thing to have. But...
Things I don't like:
- it happened 3 or 4 times for the past month that Alexa's voice broke down. It lasted only for the duration of her answer, but it sounded really bad and it was hard to understand her;
- Another thing that bothered me last week, was that Alexa was unresponsive for some time during the day. She couldn't understand me and couldn't answer me. There was no red indication for internet problems, so I assume that it was server related;
- amazon music really needs more categories for metal... just saying.

Overall, I am really happy with my purchase and I expect that those small issues will get fixed soon.
